reviews.reviewText: Said fit my Cobalt front door. Turns out a bit too thick and stoped the door panel from going back on flush. Had to remove and dremel the plastic inside panel to make it work. Does make for an easy installation if it fits. Don't forget speaker wire adapters. Not like the old days when you just wired them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect fit for 2015 Silverado with crew cab (rear doors)
reviews.reviewText: So these adapters worked perfectly for the rear speakers in my 2015 Silverado crew cab. I was worried about how far my new speakers were sticking out of the adapter compared to the originals but this adapter isn't as high/thick as the originals. I did add some velcro tape (fuzzy side) to one side of the adapters so they wouldn't rattle. I'm not sure if they would rattle but I don't want to have to take the door panels off again.I originally found these adapters that fit for my truck then clicked on the adapters + wiring harness plugs on the same product page. After getting them, I realized the wiring harness plugs are for a different year of vehicle. So be careful if you are wanting the wiring harness plugs, they might not be for the right year/make/model.
